           SPELL=ted
       BUILD_API=2
         VERSION=2.17
          SOURCE=${SPELL}-${VERSION}.src.tar.gz
SOURCE_DIRECTORY=${BUILD_DIRECTORY}/Ted-${VERSION}
        WEB_SITE=http://www.nllgg.nl/Ted
   SOURCE_URL[0]=ftp://ftp.nluug.nl/pub/editors/ted/${SOURCE}
         LICENSE=GPL
          MD5[0]=98d95fa32c020d1b9b22217c291600ec
         ENTERED=20040418
         UPDATED=20040623
SHORT="Ted is a text processor running under X Windows"
cat << EOF
Ted is an easy rich text processor. It can edit RTF files in a wysiwyg manner.
It supports multiple fonts and can print to PostScript printers.
It consists of a general part: The program, afm files and an American spelling
checker.
Additional packages with spell checkers for different languages exist.

RTF files from Ted are fully compatible with MS-Word.
Ted also is an RTF to PostScript and an RTF to
Acrobat PDF converter.
EOF
